00:33:57.183 --> 00:33:59.500 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:33:59.500 --> 00:34:02.620 align:middle line:84%
Well, um, let's get some of
the formalities out of the way.

00:34:02.620 --> 00:34:05.645 align:middle line:84%
Um, um, when were
you thinking of--

00:34:05.645 --> 00:34:07.580 align:middle line:90%
Three months.

00:34:07.580 --> 00:34:08.769 align:middle line:90%
Sorry, is that what you mean?

00:34:08.769 --> 00:34:09.469 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:34:09.469 --> 00:34:10.857 align:middle line:90%
Please, go on, yeah.

00:34:10.857 --> 00:34:15.489 align:middle line:84%
Um, yeah, in about three
to four months, if possible,

00:34:15.489 --> 00:34:18.120 align:middle line:90%
on a Sunday afternoon.

00:34:18.120 --> 00:34:22.880 align:middle line:84%
And were you planning to have
a large-- a large gathering.

00:34:22.880 --> 00:34:25.449 align:middle line:90%
No, not really.

00:34:25.449 --> 00:34:29.969 align:middle line:84%
On my side, there's my mum,
my dad died not long ago.

00:34:29.969 --> 00:34:31.440 align:middle line:90%
Mhm.

00:34:31.440 --> 00:34:32.830 align:middle line:90%
Luke doesn't have any family.

00:34:32.830 --> 00:34:34.050 align:middle line:90%
So-- I mean, well, he does--

00:34:34.050 --> 00:34:37.630 align:middle line:84%
LUKE: I'm a doctor, so my
step parents live in Denmark

00:34:37.630 --> 00:34:38.610 align:middle line:90%
and they're quite frail, so--

00:34:38.610 --> 00:34:40.391 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: We're going to
see them after the wedding.

00:34:40.391 --> 00:34:41.090 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:34:41.090 --> 00:34:44.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, since we've covered
so much ground so quickly,

00:34:44.010 --> 00:34:48.280 align:middle line:84%
I-- I think I can, um,
cut to the chase here.

00:34:48.280 --> 00:34:51.810 align:middle line:84%
What do you-- what
do both of you

00:34:51.810 --> 00:34:56.269 align:middle line:90%
hope to learn from this union?

00:34:56.269 --> 00:35:00.340 align:middle line:84%
Either about each other
or about yourself or--

00:35:00.340 --> 00:35:01.477 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Do you
want some water?

00:35:01.477 --> 00:35:02.176 align:middle line:90%
LUKE: Yeah.

00:35:02.176 --> 00:35:07.450 align:middle line:90%


00:35:07.450 --> 00:35:09.590 align:middle line:84%
Luke, would you
like to go first?

00:35:09.590 --> 00:35:18.000 align:middle line:84%
LUKE: Well-- OK, well, I
guess, um, I want to, you know,

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:22.945 align:middle line:84%
learn how to support each other,
emotionally and spiritually.

00:35:22.945 --> 00:35:25.830 align:middle line:90%


00:35:25.830 --> 00:35:29.720 align:middle line:84%
Learn how to--
know when-- when to

00:35:29.720 --> 00:35:34.990 align:middle line:84%
hold your ground and,
you know, when not to.

00:35:34.990 --> 00:35:36.130 align:middle line:90%
Fall into each other.

00:35:36.130 --> 00:35:39.016 align:middle line:90%


00:35:39.016 --> 00:35:42.490 align:middle line:84%
I think it's important
to, uh-- what's

00:35:42.490 --> 00:35:46.690 align:middle line:84%
it-- to-- to learn how to-- how
to not-- how to not fall out

00:35:46.690 --> 00:35:50.131 align:middle line:84%
of love, if you
know what I mean.

00:35:50.131 --> 00:35:50.830 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:35:50.830 --> 00:35:54.812 align:middle line:84%
That's-- that's all I can
think of at the moment.

00:35:54.812 --> 00:35:57.704 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, Luke.
Katherine?

00:35:57.704 --> 00:36:02.524 align:middle line:90%


00:36:02.524 --> 00:36:06.741 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is an interesting
question, isn't it?

00:36:06.741 --> 00:36:07.440 align:middle line:90%
Um.

00:36:07.440 --> 00:36:13.356 align:middle line:90%


00:36:13.356 --> 00:36:16.136 align:middle line:84%
Luke and I have been
together for eight years now.

00:36:16.136 --> 00:36:20.216 align:middle line:84%
And we know each other so well
and we've grown so fast so far.

00:36:20.216 --> 00:36:28.310 align:middle line:90%


00:36:28.310 --> 00:36:29.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry, I'm just not
very good at answering

00:36:29.990 --> 00:36:33.434 align:middle line:84%
these kind of questions.
Um.

00:36:33.434 --> 00:36:36.880 align:middle line:90%


00:36:36.880 --> 00:36:41.740 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to learn how
to share my-- my things

00:36:41.740 --> 00:36:44.840 align:middle line:90%
and my feelings more.

00:36:44.840 --> 00:36:47.060 align:middle line:90%
Why get married now?

00:36:47.060 --> 00:36:47.960 align:middle line:90%
But why not?

00:36:47.960 --> 00:36:49.220 align:middle line:90%
Is this an interrogation?

00:36:49.220 --> 00:36:53.230 align:middle line:90%
Um, because I love him.

00:36:53.230 --> 00:36:53.960 align:middle line:90%
He loves me.

00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:55.126 align:middle line:84%
And we know each
other really well.

00:36:55.126 --> 00:36:56.232 align:middle line:90%
That's a great answer.

00:36:56.232 --> 00:36:57.565 align:middle line:84%
Does it have to be
a complicated reason

00:36:57.565 --> 00:36:58.661 align:middle line:90%
to make something important?

00:36:58.661 --> 00:37:03.380 align:middle line:90%


00:37:03.380 --> 00:37:08.711 align:middle line:84%
OK, um, let's, um, let's
change the focus for a moment.

00:37:08.711 --> 00:37:10.830 align:middle line:84%
[PHONE RINGING]
Oh, sorry about that.

00:37:10.830 --> 00:37:12.150 align:middle line:90%
Do you mind if I get this?

00:37:12.150 --> 00:37:13.650 align:middle line:90%
No, please.

00:37:13.650 --> 00:37:17.132 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me.

00:37:17.132 --> 00:37:20.024 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't he have a
direct connection to God?

00:37:20.024 --> 00:37:20.988 align:middle line:90%
[DOOR CLOSING]

00:37:20.988 --> 00:37:23.530 align:middle line:84%
No, what business is it of
his who we are and what we do?

00:37:23.530 --> 00:37:25.270 align:middle line:84%
Brother Jackson is
just doing his job.

00:37:25.270 --> 00:37:27.630 align:middle line:90%
This is not funny.

00:37:27.630 --> 00:37:30.000 align:middle line:84%
Let's just-- no, let's
ditch the whole church thing

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:31.500 align:middle line:84%
and just get a
celibate to do it.

00:37:31.500 --> 00:37:33.500 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:35.000 align:middle line:90%
Sorry about that.

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:36.500 align:middle line:90%
You want to tell him?

00:37:36.500 --> 00:37:38.000 align:middle line:90%
FATHER NEVILLE: Where were we?

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:39.556 align:middle line:90%
Ah, yes.

00:37:39.556 --> 00:37:42.510 align:middle line:84%
Incidentally, what-- have
you discussed your plans

00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:44.880 align:middle line:90%
for starting a family?

00:37:44.880 --> 00:37:45.828 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, we have, actually.

00:37:45.828 --> 00:37:47.250 align:middle line:84%
LUKE: I don't want
to have children.

00:37:47.250 --> 00:37:50.094 align:middle line:90%


00:37:50.094 --> 00:37:53.300 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Luke, don't.

00:37:53.300 --> 00:37:54.194 align:middle line:90%
LUKE: Don't what?

00:37:54.194 --> 00:37:55.960 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: We've discussed
this previously, remember?

00:37:55.960 --> 00:37:58.800 align:middle line:84%
I know.
And I've always said no.

00:37:58.800 --> 00:38:02.426 align:middle line:84%
Well, why do you feel so
strongly about this, Luke?

00:38:02.426 --> 00:38:05.709 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Well, just tell
him about your nightmares.

00:38:05.709 --> 00:38:07.930 align:middle line:90%
He has these nightmares.

00:38:07.930 --> 00:38:10.880 align:middle line:84%
He doesn't sleep for days
about burning babies and fire.

00:38:10.880 --> 00:38:12.562 align:middle line:90%
And he's seeing a hypnotist--

00:38:12.562 --> 00:38:14.650 align:middle line:90%
OK, that is beside the point.

00:38:14.650 --> 00:38:17.130 align:middle line:84%
I just think it's-- it's
pretty simple, really.

00:38:17.130 --> 00:38:19.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, children need time
and effort and patience.

00:38:19.510 --> 00:38:23.221 align:middle line:90%


00:38:23.221 --> 00:38:24.087 align:middle line:90%
FATHER NEVILLE: Katherine?

00:38:24.087 --> 00:38:26.925 align:middle line:90%


00:38:26.925 --> 00:38:28.130 align:middle line:90%
Exactly where I--

00:38:28.130 --> 00:38:29.934 align:middle line:84%
We talked about
this five year ago.

00:38:29.934 --> 00:38:30.800 align:middle line:90%
I know, it was years ago.

00:38:30.800 --> 00:38:32.360 align:middle line:84%
Now, you bring it up
in front of a priest--

00:38:32.360 --> 00:38:33.990 align:middle line:84%
-Well, what did you expect?
-That I never met before.

00:38:33.990 --> 00:38:35.589 align:middle line:84%
What do you expect?
It's a counselling meeting.

00:38:35.589 --> 00:38:37.388 align:middle line:84%
So don't you realize when
you say things like that it

00:38:37.388 --> 00:38:38.354 align:middle line:90%
was like you rejecting me?

00:38:38.354 --> 00:38:39.620 align:middle line:84%
It's like you're
revolted by something

00:38:39.620 --> 00:38:41.188 align:middle line:84%
coming through me into
the world and just

00:38:41.188 --> 00:38:43.700 align:middle line:90%
say it in front of him.

00:38:43.700 --> 00:38:45.341 align:middle line:84%
I asked you not to
talk about our stuff.

00:38:45.341 --> 00:38:46.040 align:middle line:90%
He asked me.

00:38:46.040 --> 00:38:47.530 align:middle line:84%
Oh, since when did
you become a do-gooder?

00:38:47.530 --> 00:38:49.520 align:middle line:84%
Oh.
There's no point.

00:38:49.520 --> 00:38:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Let's just forget
the whole thing.

00:38:50.720 --> 00:38:52.830 align:middle line:84%
Katherine, please,
just calm down.

00:38:52.830 --> 00:38:54.814 align:middle line:84%
Katherine, can you just
get back in the car?

00:38:54.814 --> 00:38:55.780 align:middle line:90%
We can talk about it at home.

00:38:55.780 --> 00:38:57.120 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no.

00:38:57.120 --> 00:38:57.890 align:middle line:90%
Fine.

00:38:57.890 --> 00:39:00.804 align:middle line:84%
So you wait until my exit just
about dried up to tell me this?

00:39:00.804 --> 00:39:02.170 align:middle line:84%
I've always told you
exactly how I feel.

00:39:02.170 --> 00:39:04.240 align:middle line:84%
But if you love me,
if you really love me,

00:39:04.240 --> 00:39:05.180 align:middle line:90%
this wouldn't be an issue.

00:39:05.180 --> 00:39:06.106 align:middle line:90%
I do love you.

00:39:06.106 --> 00:39:07.180 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Oh, yeah, you
love all the easy bits,

00:39:07.180 --> 00:39:08.710 align:middle line:84%
but when it comes for hard
commitments and stuff,

00:39:08.710 --> 00:39:09.620 align:middle line:84%
you're gone.
-What?

00:39:09.620 --> 00:39:11.279 align:middle line:84%
And you think this is easy?
-See?

00:39:11.279 --> 00:39:13.860 align:middle line:84%
Even in argument,
you're insulting me.

00:39:13.860 --> 00:39:16.201 align:middle line:84%
Let's just call the
whole thing off.

00:39:16.201 --> 00:39:19.080 align:middle line:84%
Wait.
What do you mean?

00:39:19.080 --> 00:39:22.783 align:middle line:84%
If you want to be with me, you
have to have a family with me.

00:39:22.783 --> 00:39:25.248 align:middle line:84%
-You are my family.
-Bullshit.

00:39:25.248 --> 00:39:30.178 align:middle line:90%


00:39:30.178 --> 00:39:33.629 align:middle line:90%
[BELL TOLLING]

00:39:33.629 --> 00:39:52.856 align:middle line:90%


00:39:52.856 --> 00:39:54.800 align:middle line:84%
LUKE (VOICEOVER): Can we
talk about it another time?

00:39:54.800 --> 00:39:59.700 align:middle line:90%


00:39:59.700 --> 00:40:01.170 align:middle line:90%
I don't have a lot of time.

00:40:01.170 --> 00:40:04.600 align:middle line:90%


00:40:04.600 --> 00:40:07.050 align:middle line:84%
LUKE: But you want
to have a baby?

00:40:07.050 --> 00:40:09.740 align:middle line:84%
Don't you understand,
Katherine, that children

00:40:09.740 --> 00:40:13.360 align:middle line:90%
just absorb all you time?

00:40:13.360 --> 00:40:15.074 align:middle line:90%
That's what childcare is for.

00:40:15.074 --> 00:40:16.842 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no.

00:40:16.842 --> 00:40:19.460 align:middle line:84%
No, no, you can't create
something and then just reject

00:40:19.460 --> 00:40:22.756 align:middle line:90%
it just 'cause you're too busy.

00:40:22.756 --> 00:40:24.440 align:middle line:90%
They-- they feel, they absorb.

00:40:24.440 --> 00:40:26.000 align:middle line:90%
They feel everything.

00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:26.855 align:middle line:90%
They love.

00:40:26.855 --> 00:40:28.540 align:middle line:84%
It's not like a puppy
that you can just

00:40:28.540 --> 00:40:31.654 align:middle line:90%
take back when you're bored.

00:40:31.654 --> 00:40:35.680 align:middle line:84%
There's not a RSPCA
for humans, Katherine.

00:40:35.680 --> 00:40:42.526 align:middle line:90%


00:40:42.526 --> 00:40:43.504 align:middle line:90%
You're right.

00:40:43.504 --> 00:40:47.905 align:middle line:90%


00:40:47.905 --> 00:40:48.883 align:middle line:90%
You're right.

00:40:48.883 --> 00:40:54.290 align:middle line:90%


00:40:54.290 --> 00:40:56.250 align:middle line:84%
So maybe we could
practice on a dog first.

00:40:56.250 --> 00:40:57.070 align:middle line:90%
See how I go.

00:40:57.070 --> 00:41:02.300 align:middle line:90%


00:41:02.300 --> 00:41:07.414 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I could learn to do
all that grimy poo stuff.

00:41:07.414 --> 00:41:12.258 align:middle line:84%
I could walk it, and love
it, and take care of it.

00:41:12.258 --> 00:41:47.826 align:middle line:90%


00:41:47.826 --> 00:41:49.730 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be
long and cruel winter.

00:41:49.730 --> 00:41:52.352 align:middle line:90%


00:41:52.352 --> 00:41:53.640 align:middle line:90%
The moon is hanging low.

00:41:53.640 --> 00:41:58.953 align:middle line:90%


00:41:58.953 --> 00:42:03.783 align:middle line:84%
Would you be kind enough to
let me visit the village?

00:42:03.783 --> 00:42:06.210 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong?

00:42:06.210 --> 00:42:08.275 align:middle line:90%
Whose child do you carry?

00:42:08.275 --> 00:42:09.670 align:middle line:90%
Don't say that.

00:42:09.670 --> 00:42:12.720 align:middle line:84%
You woman, if it wasn't
for your devil's work,

00:42:12.720 --> 00:42:14.160 align:middle line:84%
my reputation in
the village would

00:42:14.160 --> 00:42:16.739 align:middle line:90%
still be held at high esteem.

00:42:16.739 --> 00:42:18.591 align:middle line:90%
Your spells.

00:42:18.591 --> 00:42:19.980 align:middle line:90%
And flying.

00:42:19.980 --> 00:42:20.910 align:middle line:90%
Flying.

00:42:20.910 --> 00:42:23.030 align:middle line:90%
How can you believe that?

00:42:23.030 --> 00:42:24.425 align:middle line:90%
The vicar saw you.

00:42:24.425 --> 00:42:28.540 align:middle line:84%
They saw you fly
about the trees.

00:42:28.540 --> 00:42:31.500 align:middle line:84%
Now that same group
will come for your head.

00:42:31.500 --> 00:42:34.310 align:middle line:84%
I will deliver you to
them and I will not weep.

00:42:34.310 --> 00:42:37.180 align:middle line:84%
It's your passion
that is growing in me.

00:42:37.180 --> 00:42:40.720 align:middle line:90%
It cannot be and you know that.

00:42:40.720 --> 00:42:44.005 align:middle line:84%
How can you crumble a
man's soul with such ease?

00:42:44.005 --> 00:42:47.675 align:middle line:84%
The sacrifices I have made
for you to live, and for this?

00:42:47.675 --> 00:42:51.250 align:middle line:90%


00:42:51.250 --> 00:42:54.710 align:middle line:84%
And now, everyone will
know that you've bought

00:42:54.710 --> 00:42:59.284 align:middle line:90%
the devil's child into my arms.

00:42:59.284 --> 00:43:01.280 align:middle line:90%
I am finished.

00:43:01.280 --> 00:43:02.777 align:middle line:90%
God help me.

00:43:02.777 --> 00:43:10.062 align:middle line:90%


00:43:10.062 --> 00:43:10.761 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:43:10.761 --> 00:44:02.457 align:middle line:90%


00:44:02.457 --> 00:44:03.156 align:middle line:90%
Thanks.

00:44:03.156 --> 00:44:29.603 align:middle line:90%


00:44:29.603 --> 00:44:33.096 align:middle line:90%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:44:33.096 --> 00:44:34.593 align:middle line:90%


00:44:34.593 --> 00:44:36.090 align:middle line:90%
Hello, Katherine speaking.

00:44:36.090 --> 00:44:39.320 align:middle line:90%


00:44:39.320 --> 00:44:40.718 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:44:40.718 --> 00:44:43.366 align:middle line:90%
Mum, hi, Mum.

00:44:43.366 --> 00:44:44.466 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE'S MOTHER
(ON PHONE): It

00:44:44.466 --> 00:44:45.508 align:middle line:90%
sounds like you're in the car.

00:44:45.508 --> 00:44:47.424 align:middle line:90%
Luke, darling, are you there?

00:44:47.424 --> 00:44:49.470 align:middle line:90%
Uh, yeah, I'm here.

00:44:49.470 --> 00:44:50.678 align:middle line:90%
We're just on the speakerphone.

00:44:50.678 --> 00:44:51.911 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE'S MOTHER
(ON PHONE): I just

00:44:51.911 --> 00:44:53.920 align:middle line:84%
wanted to see how
your plans were

00:44:53.920 --> 00:44:57.310 align:middle line:90%
going, if you needed any help.

00:44:57.310 --> 00:45:00.536 align:middle line:84%
No, no, Mum, it's
my nose thing.

00:45:00.536 --> 00:45:02.234 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE'S MOTHER (ON
PHONE): Oh, darling,

00:45:02.234 --> 00:45:04.509 align:middle line:90%
sounds like premarital stress.

00:45:04.509 --> 00:45:06.281 align:middle line:90%
I can never remember.

00:45:06.281 --> 00:45:09.160 align:middle line:90%
Is it head forward or back?

00:45:09.160 --> 00:45:11.226 align:middle line:90%
When can you come over?

00:45:11.226 --> 00:45:12.492 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE'S MOTHER
(ON PHONE): I could

00:45:12.492 --> 00:45:14.219 align:middle line:90%
fly down in a couple of weeks.

00:45:14.219 --> 00:45:15.640 align:middle line:90%
Would that be soon enough?

00:45:15.640 --> 00:45:18.944 align:middle line:84%
You-- could you
make-- make it sooner?

00:45:18.944 --> 00:45:21.692 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE'S MOTHER (ON
PHONE): Katie, are you there?

00:45:21.692 --> 00:45:24.020 align:middle line:90%
Why don't you take a day off?

00:45:24.020 --> 00:46:18.557 align:middle line:90%


00:46:18.557 --> 00:46:19.290 align:middle line:90%
SANDY (ON PHONE): Yup?

00:46:19.290 --> 00:46:20.970 align:middle line:84%
LUKE: Sandy, have you
seen that Fairer Day

00:46:20.970 --> 00:46:23.960 align:middle line:90%
article that was on my desk?

00:46:23.960 --> 00:46:27.370 align:middle line:90%
[DIAL TONE]

00:46:27.370 --> 00:46:33.031 align:middle line:90%


00:46:33.031 --> 00:46:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Thank you.
Sandy--

00:46:37.160 --> 00:46:44.276 align:middle line:90%


00:46:44.276 --> 00:46:45.876 align:middle line:84%
SANDY (ON PHONE): Can you
just hold on a minute?

00:46:45.876 --> 00:46:47.788 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, goodbye, Mrs. Bailey.

00:46:47.788 --> 00:46:49.110 align:middle line:90%
No, push the door.

00:46:49.110 --> 00:46:50.240 align:middle line:90%
